	â€¢	Doctrine Invoked: Procedural efficiency; implied vexatiousness.
	â€¢	Why Misapplied: Supplemental reply addressed new arguments in opposition; striking prevented fair rebuttal.
	â€¢	Correct Precedent: Courts must allow replies to new issues raised, and pro se litigants deserve leeway. See Christopher v. Harbury (denial-of-access is actionable).

